<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="668" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[168,775,1342,1503]" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,462,1342,1366]" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[607,696,1343,1366]" name="Panama" pageId="17" pageNumber="668">Panama</collectingCountry>
. It represents an extremely rare species, only six collections are known (three of them from Cerro Pirre). In the study area, this species occurs only in the cloud forests, at elevations above 
<quantity box="[322,405,1479,1503]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="17" pageNumber="668" unit="m" value="1300.0">1300 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
